<td valign="top">
<H3>Information:</H3>
<P> The Severe Weather Forecasting Exercise is an exercise in forecasting severe weather in
the United States.  

<P>The exercise simulates a severe weather forecasting event over the timespan of a day.  Users are started at 7 am and then are given hourly data
thoughout the morning until noon, when they are asked to make a forecast.

<P>Then in the afternoon, users are given hourly data that is also annotated up, so they can learn meteorological concepts.

<P>Finally, at midnight, the user's forecast is validated and they are given a score.

<HR>
<P><B>Note:</B>  Some hourly data does not exist.

